issue.title: Hotkey overlap issue
issue.body: **Describe the bug** `V` and `P` hotkeys are reserved for the `Move` and `Polygon region` tools respectively. At the same time, these hotkeys may be automatically generated for Labels https://github.com/HumanSignal/label-studio-frontend/blob/master/src/core/Hotkey.ts#L352. In such cases, the tool hotkeys have priority over Label hotkeys. **Screenshots**

issue.title: I can't span my word correctly because the symbol
issue.body:
**Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.**
I can't span my word correctly because the symbol after symbol eg: `"John Doe (Mr. Bo)"` the symbol `"` appear after symbol `)`.

**Describe the solution you'd like**
I want to label person name, eg:
`"John Doe (Mr. Bo)"`
So, the label will be `John Doe (Mr. Bo)`. But, actually in the label-studio will be `John Doe (Mr. Bo)"`. I set granulity for `Text` tag to `word`.

For example image below:
![image](https://github.com/HumanSignal/label-studio/assets/85201868/51dd00ad-cc4b-49c8-bfa4-f4416a5a8d62)

I want to not include the symbol `"` in the annotation.
